  "title": "(2\/5) Pre-Study Questionnaire",
  "body": " (2\/5) Pre-Study Questionnaire    Instructions: Please answer all questions honestly. This information helps us understand your programming background. All responses are confidential.   These are survey questions, not graded. Your response is automatically saved when you select an option— ignore the \"Check Me\" button.      Section A: Basic Information    Student ID:       School Name:       Class\/Grade:       Age:       Gender:     Male    Female    Other    Prefer not to say       Section B: Programming Self-Efficacy  For each statement, select how much you agree or disagree:    I feel confident attempting programming problems.     Strongly disagree    Disagree    Neither agree nor disagree    Agree    Strongly agree       I can do advanced work in computer science.     Strongly disagree    Disagree    Neither agree nor disagree    Agree    Strongly agree       I can learn programming.     Strongly disagree    Disagree    Neither agree nor disagree    Agree    Strongly agree       I can handle difficult programming problems.     Strongly disagree    Disagree    Neither agree nor disagree    Agree    Strongly agree       I can get good marks in computer science (CS\/IP).     Strongly disagree    Disagree    Neither agree nor disagree    Agree    Strongly agree       I am confident in my programming ability.     Strongly disagree    Disagree    Neither agree nor disagree    Agree    Strongly agree       To show you're reading carefully, please select 'Agree' for this question     Strongly disagree    Disagree    Neither agree nor disagree    Agree    Strongly agree       Section C: Concept Familiarity  For each programming concept, select your familiarity level:    Loops\/Iteration (e.g., for loops, while loops)     I am unfamiliar with this concept    I know what it means, but have not used it in a program    I have used this concept, but am not confident about my ability    I am confident in my ability to use this in simple programs    I am confident in my ability to use this in complex programs       Conditionals\/Selection Statements (e.g., if , elif , else )     I am unfamiliar with this concept    I know what it means, but have not used it in a program    I have used this concept, but am not confident about my ability    I am confident in my ability to use this in simple programs    I am confident in my ability to use this in complex programs       Functions (e.g., def function_name(): )     I am unfamiliar with this concept    I know what it means, but have not used it in a program    I have used this concept, but am not confident about my ability    I am confident in my ability to use this in simple programs    I am confident in my ability to use this in complex programs       Lists\/Arrays (e.g., my_list = [1, 2, 3] )     I am unfamiliar with this concept    I know what it means, but have not used it in a program    I have used this concept, but am not confident about my ability    I am confident in my ability to use this in simple programs    I am confident in my ability to use this in complex programs        Section D: Programming Background    How long have you been learning programming (including school classes)?     Less than 6 months    6 months to 1 year    1 to 2 years    More than 2 years       Which programming language(s) have you learned? (Check all that apply)     Python    Java    C\/C++    JavaScript    Block-based (Scratch, Blockly)    Other    None yet       If you selected \"Other\", please specify:       Have you worked with Parsons Puzzles before?  (Parsons Puzzles: rearranging code lines to form correct programs)     Yes, many times    Yes, a few times    No, this is my first time     Thank you! Please proceed to the tutorial.   "
